commitResults.messageTitle: Add main features: Greet, Echo, Exit
Automated Text UI Testing: todo, deadline, event, mark, unmark, bye
Handle errors: todo, mark, unmark, wrong commands

commitResults.messageBody:
Duke can receive commands (e.g. todo, deadline, event, bye, mark, etc.)
and save the tasks in a single session.

However, the tasks are not saved after exiting a session (entering
the command "bye").

Adding this feature allows the user to recall the tasks saved before
the current session, by saving the data into the user's hard disk.

Duke can store the deadline dates as strings for a deadline task.

To make the dates more meaningful, the dates should be stored as dates.

The dates are passed as strings, then it is parsed as date (using
java's LocalDate).

Input from user must be in the format of yyyy-mm-dd. Otherwise, it will
be invalid. Times of the deadline are not yet included in this feature.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bugs for Level-8 combined with Level-7
commitResults.messageBody:
While getting the data from the saved file, a bug will occur if the
type of task is a deadline. This is because the date format in the
saved file is MM dd yyyy instead of yyyy-mm-dd. This will cause the
constructor of the Deadline class to accept MM dd yyyy instead of
yyyy-mm-dd which will cause an error in the constructor.

To fix the error, we should change the date format in the constructor
that is being used to obtain the data from the saved file.
